    <h1>Project Guidelines</h1>

    <h2>Overview</h2>

    <p>The course project is to implement a course support product. Each project must
      include 3 features:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>ability to disseminate information about the course in a well organized manner.</li>

      <li>ability for students to submit one or more files for each assignment, tracking
        date submitted for each.</li>

      <li>ability to run an online discussion group, possibly with moderation by a
        designated individual. Each group will be required to define one or more
        additional differentiating features.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The goal of each group is to build the product as a team. During this project, I
      expect that you will learn as much about working in a team as you will about the
      software lifecycle.</p>

    <p>Each group will be responsible for a sequence of deliverables during the project:</p>

    <ul>

      <li>A product definition. Each group should feel free to propose additional
        features. I will play the role of the product manager and part of your job is to
        define the best product that can feasibly be built in the time frame given.</li>

      <li>System design.</li>

      <li>User interface. I expect that the user interface and the system design will be
        based on the versions developed by the group members for assignments 2 and 3.</li>

      <li>Schedule.</li>

      <li>Code design.</li>

      <li>2 interim status reports.</li>

      <li>Final product.</li>

    </ul>

    <p>Every member of every group must make at least one presentation in class. With the
      groups being five or six, each group's presentations must be divided between about
      two people.</p>


